HEADWORD: Sissoo
<hw>Sis*soo"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind.
<ets>s⟦imac⟧s<?/</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A leguminous tree
(<spn>Dalbergia Sissoo</spn>) of the northern parts of India; also, the
dark brown compact and durable timber obtained from it. It is used in
shipbuilding and for gun carriages, railway ties, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
